recommendation.new_prompt_text:
Decompose the problem into at most two highly focused and distinct subproblems for other agents. You must not exceed two helpers to comply with orchestration limits. Each helper should be assigned a specific, critical component of the solution (e.g., one for algorithmic logic/data structure design and one for constraint handling or edge cases). Ensure the subproblems are designed so that their results can be synthesized into a complete, final solution. Use plain text only inside helper instructions. Do not use markdown, code fences, or LaTeX-style backslashes.

Return exactly one JSON object in this format:
{
  "schema_name": "eywa_node_response",
  "schema_version": "v1",
  "orchestration_decision": "delegate",
  "decision_notes": "optional string",
  "helpers": [
    {
      "label": "helper_1",
      "instructions": "plain-text subproblem for the first helper"
    }
  ],
  "synthesis_brief": "how the parent should combine the child results"
}
